    <item>
      <title>interrupts()</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/uchastnikam/metodika/arduino-reference/functions/interrupts/interrupts/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 28 Feb 2026 10:00:00 +0300</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/uchastnikam/metodika/arduino-reference/functions/interrupts/interrupts/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Re-enables interrupts (after they’ve been disabled by &lt;a href=&#34;../nointerrupts&#34;&gt;noInterrupts()&lt;/a&gt;. Interrupts allow certain important tasks to happen in the background and are enabled by default. Some functions will not work while interrupts are disabled, and incoming communication may be ignored. Interrupts can slightly disrupt the timing of code, however, and may be disabled for particularly critical sections of code.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Syntax&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;interrupts()&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;None&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Returns&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Nothing&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example Code&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The code enables Interrupts.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-arduino&#34; data-lang=&#34;arduino&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;kt&#34;&gt;void&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;nf&#34;&gt;setup&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;{}&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;kt&#34;&gt;void&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;nf&#34;&gt;loop&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;  &lt;span class=&#34;nf&#34;&gt;noInterrupts&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;();&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;  &lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;// critical, time-sensitive code here&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;  &lt;span class=&#34;nf&#34;&gt;interrupts&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;();&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;  &lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;// other code here&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;See also&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>noInterrupts()</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/uchastnikam/metodika/arduino-reference/functions/interrupts/nointerrupts/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 28 Feb 2026 10:00:00 +0300</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/uchastnikam/metodika/arduino-reference/functions/interrupts/nointerrupts/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Disables interrupts (you can re-enable them with &lt;a href=&#34;../interrupts&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;interrupts()&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt;). Interrupts allow certain important tasks to happen in the background and are enabled by default. Some functions will not work while interrupts are disabled, and incoming communication may be ignored. Interrupts can slightly disrupt the timing of code, however, and may be disabled for particularly critical sections of code.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Syntax&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;noInterrupts()&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;None&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Returns&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Nothing&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example Code&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The code shows how to enable interrupts.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
